  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nGWU software support required visibility across inventory, academic tools, user feedback, and support-ticket operations. The team needed clearer signals for resource allocation, procurement, bottleneck detection, and response workflow improvement.\n\n## Workflow\n\nThe work moved from inventory audits and BMC Helix records into demand forecasting, dashboarding, support-ticket trend analysis, and team response improvement across Mac, Linux, and Windows environments.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Inventory audits:** conducted resource audits and supported demand forecasting through BMC Helix.\n- **Feedback dashboards:** built dashboards tracking usage and sentiment across 10+ academic tools.\n- **Ticket analytics:** analyzed support-ticket trends and operational data to identify system bottlenecks.\n- **Cross-platform support:** supported software workflows across Mac, Linux, and Windows systems.\n- **Response workflow improvement:** connected operational analysis to team response workflows and resolution tracking.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nThe work improved the operational analytics layer for GWU software support, contributing to 90%+ user satisfaction, a 97% issue resolution rate, and clearer resource-allocation and procurement signals."
